results.name: Complement obverse of n.
comment: Replace digits of n by their 9's complements, reverse the order, omit any leading zeros.
Suggested by a posting by Mike Stay to the Math Fun Mailing List, Jan 24 2016, which in turn was loosely based on the definition used in logic (see the Philosophy Pages link).
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..9999
example: The 9's complement of the digits of 980 are 019, so a(980) = 910.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jan 24 2016
ext: More terms from _Alois P. Heinz_, Jan 24 2016
